  "system": {
    "description": "<p>You gain a Breath Weapon based on your Draconic Origin. Once per Combat, you can spend <strong>2 AP</strong> to exhale in a <strong>3 Space Cone</strong> or a <strong>6 Space Line</strong>. </p><p>Alternatively, you can choose to make a Spell Attack against a single target within 6 Spaces, increasing the damage by 1.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Elemental Breath Weapon:</strong> Make a <strong>Spell Check </strong>against every target's <strong>PD </strong>within the area. <br><strong>Hit:</strong> The target takes 2 <strong>Draconic </strong>damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Mystic Breath Weapon:</strong> Make a <strong>Spell Check </strong>against every target <strong>MD </strong>within the area. <br><strong>Hit:</strong> The target takes 1 <strong>Draconic</strong> damage.</p></li></ul><p>Before you make your <strong>Spell Check</strong>, you can spend <strong>1 SP </strong>to increase the damage by 1, or <strong>1 MP</strong> to increase it by 2.</p><p>You can use this ability once between Long Rests. When you Roll for Initiative, or meet some other unique criteria at the GM's discretion, this ability recharges. </p><p></p><p><em><strong>System Tip: </strong>You need to change damage type and Defense Targeted to your selected Draconic damage in effects of that item. Default is <strong>Fire</strong>. Also if you are using Mysthic Breath Weapon reduce damage it does by 1.</em></p>",
